<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="295" pageId="5" pageNumber="294" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,796,153,215]" box="[151,235,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">
(
<figureCitation box="[160,226,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1756,1781]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Alloteratura (Meconemopsis) pentadactyla sp. nov., male: A, D. pronotum: A. dorsal view; D. lateral view; B. maxillary palpus in lateral view; C. apex of genicular lobe of postfemur; F. subgenital plate in ventral view; E, G–H. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view; G dorsal view; H. ventral view; I. epiphallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3363241/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,261,467]" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,261,288]" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body small. Fastigium verticis conical, apex bluntly rounded. Eyes nearly globular, protrud- ing forward. Apical segment of maxillary palpi shorter, about 1/3 length of subapical one, apex enlarged (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1422,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1756,1781]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Alloteratura (Meconemopsis) pentadactyla sp. nov., male: A, D. pronotum: A. dorsal view; D. lateral view; B. maxillary palpus in lateral view; C. apex of genicular lobe of postfemur; F. subgenital plate in ventral view; E, G–H. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view; G dorsal view; H. ventral view; I. epiphallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3363241/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Anterior margin of pronotum nearly straight, posterior margin angularly rounded, lateral lobe longer than high; humeral sinus distinct (
<figureCitation box="[412,502,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1756,1781]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Alloteratura (Meconemopsis) pentadactyla sp. nov., male: A, D. pronotum: A. dorsal view; D. lateral view; B. maxillary palpus in lateral view; C. apex of genicular lobe of postfemur; F. subgenital plate in ventral view; E, G–H. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view; G dorsal view; H. ventral view; I. epiphallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3363241/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Thoracic foramen large, oval, exposed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,261,467]" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">Tegmina long, surpassing apices of postfemora, basal area comparatively wider, then gradually narrowing, apices rounded. Hind wings slightly longer than tegmina.</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3363241/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="294" startId="5.[151,250,1756,1781]" targetBox="[151,1436,489,1737]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1756,1853]" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1756,1781]" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">FIGURE 3</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1922" box="[286,586,1757,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Alloteratura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Meconemopsis">
<emphasis box="[286,411,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">Alloteratura</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[428,579,1758,1781]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">Meconemopsis</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
p 
<emphasis box="[608,745,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">
entadactyla 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[735,745,1758,1781]" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">s</emphasis>
</emphasis>
p. nov., male: A, D. pronotum: A. dorsal view; D. lateral view; B. maxillary palpus in lateral view; C. apex of genicular lobe of postfemur; F. subgenital plate in ventral view; E, G–H. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view; G dorsal view; H. ventral view; I. epiphallus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1899,2034]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,152,827]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="295" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">
All femora without spines on ventral surface, apices of genicular lobes of profemora and mesofemora bluntly rounded. Procoxae with 1 short spine; protibiae with 4–6 spines on internal and external margins of ventral surface separately; tibial tympana open on both sides and oval. Mesotibiae with 2–6 spines on internal and external margins of ventral surface separately. Apices of genicular lobes of postfemora with 1 spine on both sides. (
<figureCitation box="[1269,1358,2007,2034]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1756,1781]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Alloteratura (Meconemopsis) pentadactyla sp. nov., male: A, D. pronotum: A. dorsal view; D. lateral view; B. maxillary palpus in lateral view; C. apex of genicular lobe of postfemur; F. subgenital plate in ventral view; E, G–H. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view; G dorsal view; H. ventral view; I. epiphallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3363241/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="294">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
), post- tibiae with 29–35 spines on internal and external margins of dorsal surface separately, 2 pairs of dorsal apical spurs and 1 pair of ventral apical spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">
Tenth abdominal tergite nearly rectangle, longer than broad, the middle area of posterior margin concave (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1756,1781]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Alloteratura (Meconemopsis) pentadactyla sp. nov., male: A, D. pronotum: A. dorsal view; D. lateral view; B. maxillary palpus in lateral view; C. apex of genicular lobe of postfemur; F. subgenital plate in ventral view; E, G–H. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view; G dorsal view; H. ventral view; I. epiphallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3363241/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
). Cercus stout, the middle area curved dorsally, inner margin concave, apical area slender, apex obtusely rounded (
<figureCitation box="[160,252,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1756,1781]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Alloteratura (Meconemopsis) pentadactyla sp. nov., male: A, D. pronotum: A. dorsal view; D. lateral view; B. maxillary palpus in lateral view; C. apex of genicular lobe of postfemur; F. subgenital plate in ventral view; E, G–H. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view; G dorsal view; H. ventral view; I. epiphallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3363241/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
). Epiphallus posterior margin with rectangular notch in the middle, inner margins with five sclerotized spines directing dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[438,515,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1756,1781]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,489,1737]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Alloteratura (Meconemopsis) pentadactyla sp. nov., male: A, D. pronotum: A. dorsal view; D. lateral view; B. maxillary palpus in lateral view; C. apex of genicular lobe of postfemur; F. subgenital plate in ventral view; E, G–H. apex of abdomen: E. lateral view; G dorsal view; H. ventral view; I. epiphallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3363241/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">
Fig. 
<date box="[490,515,333,359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">3I</date>
</figureCitation>
). Basal half of subgenital plate with a longitudinal furrow in the midline; basal and apical areas broad while middle area slightly narrower, apical half broken.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,404,431]" pageId="6" pageNumber="295">Colouration.</emphasis>
Body yellowish green (green when alive). Fastigium verticis dark. Eyes brown. Ventral surface of antennal scape dark brown. Dorsum of epicranium with a Y-shaped brown spot. Spines of legs blackish brown, tarsus green. Tegmina and the exposed parts of hind wings green.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
